&lt;p&gt;In Python, &lt;code&gt;print&lt;/code&gt; will add a &lt;code&gt;\n&lt;/code&gt; or space. How can I avoid that? I&apos;d like to know how to &quot;append&quot; strings to &lt;code&gt;stdout&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
